            <title>[SOLR-15340] rename shardsWhitelist to allowUrls and move to top of solr.xml</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15340</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;shardsWhitelist&lt;/tt&gt; is defined on shardHandlerFactory element in solr.xml. We should rename it so something like &quot;allowUrls&quot;. And we could use it in more places.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://solr.apache.org/guide/8_7/distributed-requests.html#configuring-the-shardhandlerfactory&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://solr.apache.org/guide/8_7/distributed-requests.html#configuring-the-shardhandlerfactory&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(this is split off from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15217&quot; title=&quot;use shardsWhitelist in ReplicationHandler&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-15217&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-15217&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
